UID:18419-1773252000-1773255600@jcceastbay.org
SUMMARY:Hebrew Community Talk: Superconductivity
DESCRIPTION:מוליכות על — פיסיקה קוונטית בגודל טבעי\nברוכים הבאים אל העולם המוזר של הפיסיקה הקוונטית. מהי מוליכות-על? כיצד היא יכולה להביא לפיתוח רכבות מרחפות ויישומים רפואיים מתקדמים?\nHebrew Community Talk: Superconductivity: Life-Size Quantum Physics\n(NOTE: TALK WILL BE PRESENTED IN HEBREW) \nFirst in a new series of talks where Israeli members of Madurat HaShevat share their professional expertise through engaging\, high-level lectures. \nThe kickoff program will be presented by Ella Lachman\, who holds a PhD in Condensed Matter Physics\, and who completed her postdoctoral studies at the Quantum Materials lab at UC Berkeley. \nHer talk “Superconductivity: Life-Size Quantum Physics” is designed to be accessible and interesting for a general audience. \nFree. Registration required. \nCLICK HERE TO REGISTER\nHospitality sponsored by Science Abroad
URL:https://jcceastbay.org/events/hebrew-community-talk-superconductivity/
LOCATION:JCC East Bay\, 1414 Walnut Street\, Berkeley\, CA\, 94709\, United States
CATEGORIES:Civic Engagement,Jewish Life
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://jcceastbay.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/hebrew-talk-superconductivity.png
END:VEVENT
