BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Magnes": "https://magnes.berkeley.edu/program/history-is-calling-celebrating-130-years-of-jewish-history-in-the-bay-area/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:magnes
X-SOURCE:Magnes
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260322T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260322T160000
DTSTAMP:20260310T152201
CREATED:20260220T195917Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260309T173426Z
UID:10001079-1774184400-1774195200@magnes.berkeley.edu
SUMMARY:History is Calling! Celebrating 130 Years  of Jewish History in the Bay Area
DESCRIPTION:Presented by J. The Jewish News of Northern California and the Magnes Collection of Jewish Art and Life. \nJoin the J. and the Magnes for a free\, family-friendly afternoon of programs and activities celebrating 130 Years of Jewish History in the Bay Area. \n\nBe a part of our audio history project: Record a voice mail sharing your Jewish history story.\nHear from local archivists Susan Morris and Lara Michels as they look back at Jewish identity and culture in the Bay Area\nDive into Bay Area Jewish history with a hands-on\, family-friendly art workshop\nDiscover local Jewish material culture and journalism from the Magnes collection and the J’s archive.\nConnect with the community during a reception with light refreshments\n\n  \nSunday\, March 22\, 2026 | 1:00-4:00 pm\nat the Magnes Collection of Jewish Art and Life\, 2121 Allston Way\, Berkeley\, CA \nActivities and Reception begin at 1:00pm\nHistorian Panel begins at 2:30pm \nRSVP \n  \nFor questions about accessibility or require accommodations to participate in this event\, please reach out to magnes@berkeley.edu or (510) 643-2526 with as much advance notice as possible. \n  \nAbout the Panelists \nLara Michels is an archivist and historian. She serves as Head of Archival Processing at The Bancroft Library\, where she oversees work on all of Bancroft’s archival collections\, including those of the Magnes’ former Western Jewish History Center. She has also been an archivist at the Pacific Gas & Electric Company and at the Judah L. Magnes Museum. \nSusan Morris is a a former archivist and curator in the Western Jewish History Center\, Judah Magnes Museum\, Berkeley. She served as Executive Director of the Judah Magnes Museum following the retirement of Seymour Fromer\, Magnes museum co-founder. Susan is the author of A Traveler’s Guide to Pioneer Jewish Cemeteries of the California Gold Rush. She is a Rosston Society member of the UC Berkeley University Library.
URL:https://magnes.berkeley.edu/program/history-is-calling-celebrating-130-years-of-jewish-history-in-the-bay-area/
LOCATION:Magnes Collection of Jewish Life and Art\, 2121 Allston Way\, Berkeley\, CA\, 94720\, United States
CATEGORIES:Families,Home Page Event,Open House,Panel Discussion,PopUp Exhibition
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://magnes.berkeley.edu/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/HistoryIsCalling_16-9.jpg
ORGANIZER;CN="Magnes Collection of Jewish Art and Life":MAILTO:magnes@berkeley.edu
END:VEVENT
