X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Jcc East Bay": "https://jcceastbay.org/events/hands-on-passover-cooking-workshop/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:jcc_east_bay
X-SOURCE:Jcc East Bay
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260323T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260323T210000
DTSTAMP:20260311T074614
CREATED:20260303T190504Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260305T200006Z
UID:18365-1774288800-1774299600@jcceastbay.org
SUMMARY:Hands-On Passover Cooking Workshop
DESCRIPTION:Hands-On Passover Cooking Workshop with Aliza Grayevsky Somekh of Bishulim SF\nEarly-bird registration by 3/16 $150 per person; after 3/17 $180 per person | Registration required | Limited to 12 adults\nJoin Chef Aliza for an intimate\, hands-on Passover cooking workshop that explores the rich ritual and cultural diversity of the Seder table. Together\, we’ll prepare a festive Passover meal inspired by Jewish communities from around the world\, learning traditional dishes and creative contemporary interpretations along the way. \nUsing the symbols of the Seder plate as our inspiration\, Aliza will weave tradition into modern recipes for the holiday meal. Participants will cook the dishes and prepare several versions of charoset from different Jewish traditions and communities\, while discovering new spices\, flavors\, and stories from across the Jewish world. \nWe’ll cook side by side\, then sit down together to enjoy the meal we’ve prepared\, share stories of the holiday\, and connect around the table. \nThe event will take place at a private house in the El Cerrito Hills. Directions will be provided after tickets are purchased. \nWorkshop is kosher-style meat format meaning there will be no mixing of meat and dairy. The meat used will be meat that is permitted to eat\, but it will not have a kosher certification. \nPURCHASE TICKETS HERE\nAbout Aliza\nAliza Grayevsky Somekh\, an Israeli educator and chef. She is an eighth-generation Jerusalemite. Aliza specializes in Israeli culture. After a long career in informal education and Israeli culture working with U.S and Israel-based Jewish organizations In 2016\, she opened Bishulim SF\, a boutique catering company fusing California ingredients with Israeli flavors. Drawing from her roots and culinary expertise\, she creates food experiences that highlight Israel’s diverse heritage and tell meaningful stories\, building connections through cuisine. \nWebsite: bishulimsf.com \nInstagram: instagram.com/bishulim_sf
URL:https://jcceastbay.org/events/hands-on-passover-cooking-workshop/
LOCATION:CA
CATEGORIES:Jewish Life,PASSOVER
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://jcceastbay.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/passover-cooking-workshop.jpg
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Kehilla": "https://kehillasynagogue.org/event/the-torah-of-place-and-diaspora/2026-03-23/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:kehilla
X-SOURCE:Kehilla
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260323T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260323T210000
DTSTAMP:20260311T044642
CREATED:20260108T213305Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260210T192653Z
UID:10006004-1774292400-1774299600@kehillasynagogue.org
SUMMARY:The Torah of Place and Diaspora
DESCRIPTION:  \nRegister Here \nTaught by: Rabbi Dev Noily \nWeekly on Mondays from 7-9 pm for 6 sessions\, in person only\, starting on February 16th. \nDescription: \nWhat does the Torah teach about our relationship to land and about how we are to live with integrity and in harmony with the land? What’s the role of the land of Israel/Palestine in the covenantal relationship between the Jewish people and YHVH / G-d? How does Torah and later Jewish teaching guide us in our experience as Jews living in\, and embracing diaspora?  \nTogether we will study both sacred Jewish texts and current scholarship that is (re-)revealing Jewish diaspora and exile as generative\, creative and necessary – both physically and spiritually – for Jewish thriving. There will be a modest amount of reading to do between sessions. \nPlease note: This class is not a drop-in course. Students must register for the full series. Please arrive early. We will start welcoming people 30 minutes before class and will conclude 30 minutes after class begins. \nDates: \n\nMon.\, February 16\nMon.\, February 23\n\n((no class on March 2nd))\n\n\nMon.\, March 9\nMon.\, March 16\nMon.\, March 23\nMon.\, March 30\n\n  \nCost:*  \nMembers – $192 for all sessions \nNon-Members – $240 for all sessions \n*No one turned away for lack of ability to pay; please pay what you can at registration or email Rabbi SAM if you need a full discount. \nRegister Here \nPlease email Rabbi SAM Luckey at rabbisam@kehillasynagogue.org if you have any questions about registration. \nIMPORTANT! PLEASE READ: Kehilla’s COVID Public Health Protocols here.\nAll events at Kehilla are scent-free. Click here for information about what it means to be scent-free. \n 
URL:https://kehillasynagogue.org/event/the-torah-of-place-and-diaspora/2026-03-23/
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://kehillasynagogue.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/a-3-1.png
END:VEVENT
