SUMMARY:Alef Bet & Beyond!
DESCRIPTION:Taught by Rabbi SAM Luckey  \n  \nWeekly on Thursday evenings from 7:30 to 8:45 pm ONLINE for 5 sessions \nCome learn to decode the alef-bet! In this five week course\, we will learn the Hebrew letters and vowels using fun visual and aural mnemonics. Home practice between classes is highly encouraged. \nWhether this is your first encounter with the alef-bet or a refresher\, we will build a foundation for reading sacred Hebrew (and Aramaic) texts such as Torah\, Talmud\, and liturgy. This class will prepare you to join a trope class\, a 700 Benches Beit Midrash (house of study) class\, or other workshops that involve studying Hebrew or Aramaic texts in their original languages.  \nDates: \nFebruary 26 \nMarch 5\, 12\, 19\, 26 \nCost:* \n\nMembers: $100 for series\nNon-members: $125 for series\n\n → Plus a workbook that costs $6-15\, ordered separately \nNote: You will need to get a copy of the book L’shon Ha-Kodesh. You can find used copies on the internet for $6-15.  \n  \n*No one turned away for lack of ability to pay; please pay what you can at registration or email Rabbi SAM if you need a full discount. \n  \nREGISTER HERE  \nPlease email Rabbi SAM Luckey at rabbisam@kehillasynagogue.org if you have any questions. \n 
URL:https://kehillasynagogue.org/event/alef-bet-beyond-5/2026-03-26/
END:VEVENT
