SUMMARY:Passover Family Festival
DESCRIPTION:Urban Adamah offers an ever-expanding calendar of community programs that integrate mind\, heart\, and body. Join us for a Shabbat celebration or other Jewish events and holidays\, a volunteer work party\, a gardening workshop\, a family farm day\, and so much more. We hope to see you on the farm soon!				\n				\n				\n				\n							\n			\n		\n						\n				\n				\n				\n									Looking for ways to bring the farm home? Looking for new ways to celebrate an upcoming holiday? Or curious about past programs offerings? Check out our virtual resource guide for various at-home gardening tips\, nature based projects for the entire family\, and programs that create spiritual connection\, and so much more! 								\n				\n				\n				\n									\n					\n						\n									Virtual Resource Guide\n					\n					\n				\n								\n				\n				\n				\n							\n			\n		\n						\n				\n				\n				\n					Filter Events By:				\n				\n				\n				\n									\n					  Youth & FamiliesFarming & NatureShabbat & HolidaysMindfulnessJewish LearningMusic & FilmRetreats		\n		\n						\n				\n					\n		\n					\n		\n					\n		\n					\n		\n				\n						\n					\n			\n						\n				\n							\n	\n\n			\n			\n\n				\n					\n						Jan 21\, 7:00pm -\n						Dec 10\, 8:30pm\n					\n				\n\n\n\n				\n					\n						Rosh Chodesh Circle Series\n\n						\n											\n\n					Join us for our monthly Rosh Chodesh gatherings\, an opportunity to come together and get rooted in our Jewish tradition and the natural land cycles. Each session is crafted to correspond with the new ... \n\n					Learn More\n				\n			\n		\n\n			\n			\n\n				\n					\n						March 14\n						10:00am - 4:00pm\n					\n				\n\n\n\n				\n					\n						Spring Farm Intensive with Caleb O’Reilly\n\n						\n											\n\n					Join us this spring at Urban Adamah for a home-scale farming intensive designed to deepen not just your skills\, but your relationship with the living world around you.\n\nThis first installment of a... \n\n					Learn More\n				\n			\n		\n\n			\n			\n\n				\n					\n						March 15\n						5:00pm - 9:00pm\n					\n				\n\n\n\n				\n					\n						Berkeley Supper Club – March\n\n						\n											\n\n					This dinner is about the transition between winter and spring. The conversations shaping the menu are still in progress\, and it is becoming another thoughtful and bountiful meal.\nAs always\, this is a... \n\n					Learn More\n				\n			\n		\n\n			\n			\n\n				\n					\n						Mar 18\, 4:00pm -\n						Apr 8\, 6:30pm\n					\n				\n\n\n\n				\n					\n						Effective Communication for Difficult Conversations: A Virtual NVC Workshop with Adam Berman\n\n						\n											\n\n					Essential Tools for Difficult Conversations:\nA Live\, Practice-Based NVC Introductory Workshop\nThree Wednesdays\, March 18\, 25 and April 8\, 2026\n4:00 PM to 6:30 PM (PST)\n$395 per person\n\nLearn pra... \n\n					Learn More\n				\n			\n		\n\n			\n			\n\n				\n					\n						March 19\n						7:00pm - 8:30pm\n					\n				\n\n\n\n				\n					\n						Nisan Rosh Chodesh Circle\n\n						\n											\n\n					Join us for our monthly Rosh Chodesh gatherings\, an opportunity to come together and get rooted in our Jewish tradition and the natural land cycles. Each session is crafted to correspond with the new ... \n\n					Learn More\n				\n			\n		\n\n			\n			\n\n				\n					\n						March 23\n						11:00am - 1:00pm\n					\n				\n\n\n\n				\n					\n						Babies on the Farm!\n\n						\n											\n\n					Welcome to our drop-in group for babies and their parents! We will meet to shmooze\, play and enjoy some music and Boichik bagels. You are welcome to come late or leave early. This is meant to be an i... \n\n					Learn More\n				\n			\n		\n\n			\n			\n\n				\n					\n						March 24\n						7:00pm - 9:00pm\n					\n				\n\n\n\n				\n					\n						Finding Your Freedom – a PJ Library Passover Program for Parents\n\n						\n											\n\n					Join Jamie Greenwood\, somatic life + leadership coach\, for an interactive workshop exploring the Passover theme of freedom and how we can reclaim that freedom in our day-to-day lives for greater conne... \n\n					Learn More\n				\n			\n		\n\n			\n			\n\n				\n					\n						March 26\n						6:30pm - 8:30pm\n					\n				\n\n\n\n				\n					\n						Releasing the Pharaoh Within: A Kundalini Yoga Workshop Inspired by Astrology\n\n						\n											\n\n					Many of us have external freedoms\, but consistently struggle with various levels of dread and worry. Supported by the story of Passover\, we'll be exploring how to shift these patterns. Along with Yoga... \n\n					Learn More\n				\n			\n		\n\n			\n			\n\n				\n					\n						March 27\n						5:30pm - 6:30pm\n					\n				\n\n\n\n				\n					\n						Tot Shabbat w. Mimi Greisman!\n\n						\n											\n\n					Join Urban Adamah and Mimi Greisman for Tot Shabbat on the farm where little ones and their grown-ups come together to celebrate\, sing\, and make new friends! With joyful songs\, playful movement\, and i... \n\n					Learn More\n				\n			\n		\n\n			\n			\n\n				\n					\n						March 27\n						6:30pm - 8:30pm\n					\n				\n\n\n\n				\n					\n						Kabbalat Shabbat\n\n						\n											\n\n					Join Urban Adamah for our signature Friday night service! Through song\, poetry\, movement\, and silence we’ll journey together from our week of doing into our day of being. All are welcome. No Hebrew ... \n\n					Learn More\n				\n			\n		\n\n		\n\n	\n		\n		Next Page
URL:https://urbanadamah.org/event/passover-family-festival-2026329/
