X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Kehilla": "https://kehillasynagogue.org/event/the-torah-of-place-and-diaspora/2026-03-30/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:kehilla
X-SOURCE:Kehilla
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260330T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260330T210000
DTSTAMP:20260311T044642
CREATED:20260108T213305Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260210T192653Z
UID:10006005-1774897200-1774904400@kehillasynagogue.org
SUMMARY:The Torah of Place and Diaspora
DESCRIPTION:  \nRegister Here \nTaught by: Rabbi Dev Noily \nWeekly on Mondays from 7-9 pm for 6 sessions\, in person only\, starting on February 16th. \nDescription: \nWhat does the Torah teach about our relationship to land and about how we are to live with integrity and in harmony with the land? What’s the role of the land of Israel/Palestine in the covenantal relationship between the Jewish people and YHVH / G-d? How does Torah and later Jewish teaching guide us in our experience as Jews living in\, and embracing diaspora?  \nTogether we will study both sacred Jewish texts and current scholarship that is (re-)revealing Jewish diaspora and exile as generative\, creative and necessary – both physically and spiritually – for Jewish thriving. There will be a modest amount of reading to do between sessions. \nPlease note: This class is not a drop-in course. Students must register for the full series. Please arrive early. We will start welcoming people 30 minutes before class and will conclude 30 minutes after class begins. \nDates: \n\nMon.\, February 16\nMon.\, February 23\n\n((no class on March 2nd))\n\n\nMon.\, March 9\nMon.\, March 16\nMon.\, March 23\nMon.\, March 30\n\n  \nCost:*  \nMembers – $192 for all sessions \nNon-Members – $240 for all sessions \n*No one turned away for lack of ability to pay; please pay what you can at registration or email Rabbi SAM if you need a full discount. \nRegister Here \nPlease email Rabbi SAM Luckey at rabbisam@kehillasynagogue.org if you have any questions about registration. \nIMPORTANT! PLEASE READ: Kehilla’s COVID Public Health Protocols here.\nAll events at Kehilla are scent-free. Click here for information about what it means to be scent-free. \n 
URL:https://kehillasynagogue.org/event/the-torah-of-place-and-diaspora/2026-03-30/
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://kehillasynagogue.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/a-3-1.png
END:VEVENT
