DESCRIPTION:<h3>Judaism is built around community\, ritual\, tradition\, an
 d prayer. If you are Jewish\, interested in converting or raising a Jewish 
 family and looking to learn more\, delve deeper\, and connect — learn with 
 us! </h3><p>Our<a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://maascenter.aju
 .edu/introduction-to-judaism/&amp\;sa=D&amp\;source=calendar&amp\;ust=17614
 33613667886&amp\;usg=AOvVaw37XQkC0t7tZXnnyCF0qP1z" target="_blank"><u><u> <
 em>engaging\, university-accredited Intro To Judaism course</em></u></u></a
 > is interactive and encourages questions\, discussion\, and hands-on learn
 ing. No knowledge of Hebrew is required. This Introduction to Judaism class
  will be taught in three units. For those who are on the path for conversio
 n\, please register for the full course — all three units\, as this is not 
 a drop-in model. </p><p><a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.b
 ethsholomsf.org/intro-to-judaism&amp\;sa=D&amp\;source=calendar&amp\;ust=17
 61433613667886&amp\;usg=AOvVaw2-G5v30-odLm3OvJLECXlA" target="_blank"><u>Cl
 ick here for schedule and registration! </u></a></p><p>Looking to join our 
 next cohort in the fall? Contact Hilary at <a href="mailto:helfman@bethshol
 omsf.org?" target="_blank"><u>helfman@bethsholomsf.org</u></a> for more inf
 ormation</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20251020T230717Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Intro to Judaism Unit 3
